detailedDescription.articleBody: Susan Alexandra "Sigourney" Weaver is an American actress. Weaver is considered to be a pioneer of action heroines in science fiction films.

Esther Hicks, often credited as Abraham Hicks, is an American inspirational speaker and author. She has co-written nine books with her late husband Jerry Hicks, presented numerous workshops on the law of attraction with Abraham Hicks Publications and appeared in the original version of the 2006 film The Secret.

detailedDescription.articleBody: Jacqueline Ruth Weaver AO is an Australian theatre, film, and television actress. She is known internationally for her performances in Animal Kingdom and Silver Linings Playbook, both of which earned her nominations for an Academy Award for Best Supporting Actress.

detailedDescription.articleBody: Silas Marner: The Weaver of Raveloe is the third novel by Mary Ann Evans. It was published in 1861. An outwardly simple tale of a linen weaver, it is notable for its strong realism and its sophisticated treatment of a variety of issues ranging from religion to industrialisation to community.
detailedDescription.articleBodyHi: सिलास मार्नर: द वीवर ऑफ रेवेलो मैरी एन इवांस का तीसरा उपन्यास है, यह 1861 में प्रकाशित हुआ था, एक लिनन बुनकर की एक बाहरी रूप से सरल कहानी, यह अपने मजबूत यथार्थवाद और धर्म से लेकर विभिन्न मुद्दों के परिष्कृत उपचार के लिए उल्लेखनीय है।

detailedDescription.articleBody: Jennifer Love Hewitt is an American actress, producer and singer. Hewitt began her career as a child actress and singer, appearing in national television commercials before joining the cast of the Disney Channel series Kids Incorporated.
